Your flow is actually working correctly now.

The problem is only this:

```text
POST /arthur-core/sales-points/select
→ 404 Not Found
```

Which means your HTML form action and controller mapping do not match.

From logs:

```text
POST /arthur-core/sales-points/select
404
```

So either:

* controller path is wrong
* or class-level `@RequestMapping` is missing/mismatched

---

# Most likely fix

Your controller probably has:

```java
@Controller
@RequestMapping("/sales-points")
public class SalesPointController
```

Then method:

```java
@PostMapping("/select")
```

Final URL becomes:

```text
/sales-points/select
```

BUT your application already has context path:

```text
/arthur-core
```

So Thymeleaf form should be:

```html
<form method="post" th:action="@{/sales-points/select}">
```

NOT:

```html
<form action="/arthur-core/sales-points/select">
```

Because Spring automatically prefixes the context path.

---

# Correct Thymeleaf

Use:

```html
<form method="post" th:action="@{/sales-points/select}">
```

And radio:

```html
<input type="radio"
       name="salesPointId"
       th:value="${sp.id}"
       required>
```

---

# Correct controller

```java
@Controller
@RequestMapping("/sales-points")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class SalesPointController {

    private final AuthService authService;

    @PostMapping("/select")
    public void selectSalesPoint(
            @CookieValue("ARTHUR_SESSION") String sessionId,
            @RequestParam String salesPointId,
            HttpServletResponse response
    ) throws IOException {

        String redirectUrl =
                authService.completeSalesPointSelection(sessionId, salesPointId);

        response.sendRedirect(redirectUrl);
    }
}
```

---

# Why this happened

You currently have BOTH:

```text
context-path = /arthur-core
```

AND probably hardcoded:

```html
action="/arthur-core/sales-points/select"
```

which can create mismatches depending on deployment.

Using Thymeleaf `@{}` is the correct Spring way.
